record.title: QUESTION OF THE PRIVILEGES OF THE HOUSE

speaking-unknown-id.title: Mr.
speaking-unknown-id.name: BOEHNER
speaking-unknown-id.paragraph: Madam Speaker, I have a privileged resolution at the desk.

record.chair: The Clerk will report the resolution.
The resolution constitutes a question of privilege.

speaking-unknown-id.title: Mr.
speaking-unknown-id.name: HOYER
speaking-unknown-id.paragraph: Madam Speaker, I move to table the resolution.

speaking-unknown-id.title: Mr.
speaking-unknown-id.name: BOEHNER
speaking-unknown-id.paragraph: Madam Speaker, I raise a point of order that the gentleman from Maryland engaged in debate.

record.chair: The question is on the motion to table.
The gentleman will state his inquiry.

speaking-unknown-id.title: Mr.
speaking-unknown-id.name: BOEHNER
speaking-unknown-id.paragraph: Madam Speaker, isn't it correct that the gentleman from Maryland engaged in debate, which allows the House to then proceed with up to 1 hour of debate on this resolution?

record.chair: The gentleman was not recognized as the Chair had not yet ruled that the resolution constituted a question of privilege.

speaking-unknown-id.title: Mr.
speaking-unknown-id.name: BOEHNER
speaking-unknown-id.paragraph: Madam Speaker, on that I demand the yeas and nays.

record.narrative: The yeas and nays were ordered.
